        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 6:50PM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 650 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Heartwell to near Funk to near Bertrand.
Movement was north at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Bertrand, Loomis, and Heartwell around 655 PM CDT.
Kearney and Gibbon around 700 PM CDT.
Elm Creek, Overton, and Odessa around 705 PM CDT.
Shelton and Riverdale around 710 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of these storms include Amherst,
Pleasanton, Miller, Poole and Sumner.

This includes Interstate 80 between mile markers 239 and 292.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT for
south central Nebraska.</instruction>
